# SAQ Engine Rules

Applies when editing `src/lib/saq/` and `src/lib/saq/engine/`.

## Module Responsibilities

- `scoring.ts`: foundational scoring and priority helpers/types.
- `results.ts`: builds assessment results/summaries from scope + answers.
- `actions.ts`: builds action-plan items and implementation summaries from results + action metadata.
- `interpretation.ts`: converts results/action summaries into stakeholder-readable interpretation text.

## Guardrails

- Keep business logic centralized in engine modules; avoid logic drift into components.
- Preserve type-level contracts used by dashboard/report/assessment flow.
- Prefer additive, well-scoped changes over broad rewrites in scoring semantics.
- If changing formulas, thresholds, or priority mapping, update tests/docs in the same change.
- Do not couple engine code to database access (Postgres/Drizzle, Supabase clients), Next.js, or UI concerns.
